DATA CLOUD
Create a Data Share

Select the Data Cloud objects that you want to include in a data share to share with a third-party partner.

REQUIRED USER PERMISSIONS
USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To create data shares:	Data Cloud Admin or Data Aware Specialist

To comply with data policies and regulations, data sharing includes the IndividualGDPRState__dll object, which provides individuals with consent information. You can use Individual ID to link and honor the consent data for an individual at the data share target.

In Data Cloud, on the Data Shares tab, click New.
Enter these details and click Next .
Label - The display name of the data share. For Google BigQuery, the character limit is 20, but you can add details in Description. For Snowflake, there’s no character limit.
Name - The API name for the data share in Data Cloud. It's auto-populated to match the label name. You can choose to use a different name.
Data Space - A data space is a logical partition to organize your data for profile unification, insights, and marketing in Data Cloud. Choose “Default” for data space if you don’t have any other data space provisioned in your org.
Description - Any relevant details of the data share.
Select the Data Cloud objects that you want to include.
Click Save.

You see a success message when the data share is created.
